# IAM production surface map (inneranimalmedia.com)

**Canonical Worker entry:** `src/index.js` (not `worker.js`).  
**Deploy:** `npm run deploy:full` → `scripts/deploy-frontend.sh` (Vite → R2 `static/dashboard/app/` + `wrangler deploy -c wrangler.production.toml`).

## How agents should ask for / refresh the filetree

Do **not** guess routes or folder layout from memory. Use this order:

1. **This rule** — URL → file map below.
2. **Worker public HTML map** — `ASSET_ROUTES` in `src/index.js` (~line 307).
3. **Dashboard React routes** — `dashboard/App.tsx` (`<Routes>` ~3025+; auth routes ~353+).
4. **API dispatch** — `src/core/production-dispatch.js` → `src/api/*.js`.
5. **Regenerate stale API index (optional):** `npm run generate:route-map` → `docs/codebase-index/ws_inneranimalmedia/route-map.md` (may lag; verify against `src/index.js`).
6. **Tree commands (repo root only):**
   ```bash
   pwd  # must end with inneranimalmedia
   find src/api src/core dashboard/pages dashboard/components -maxdepth 2 -type d | sort
   ls -1 src/api/*.js | wc -l
   ```

## Repo layout (runtime)

| Area | Path | Ships to |
|------|------|----------|
| Worker + routing | `src/index.js`, `src/core/production-dispatch.js` | Cloudflare Worker |
| HTTP handlers | `src/api/` (~113 modules) | Worker |
| Agent / workflow core | `src/core/workflow-executor.js`, `src/core/provider.js`, `src/do/` | Worker |
| Dashboard SPA | `dashboard/` (Vite React) | R2 `inneranimalmedia` prefix `static/dashboard/app/` |
| Public marketing HTML | R2 **`ASSETS`** keys under `pages/*` (not in git; mapped in Worker) | `env.ASSETS` |
| Migrations / D1 truth | `migrations/*.sql` | D1 `inneranimalmedia-business` |
| MCP server (separate worker) | `inneranimalmedia-mcp-server/` (sibling deploy) | `mcp.inneranimalmedia.com` |

**Dashboard build output:** `dashboard/dist/` → uploaded as `/static/dashboard/app/*`. SPA shell: `dashboard.html` (or index) via `getDashboardSpaHtmlShell()` in Worker.

## Auth model (important)

| Path prefix | Server gate | Notes |
|-------------|-------------|-------|
| `/dashboard`, `/dashboard/*` | **Session required** in `src/index.js` (~763–771); else redirect `/auth/login?next=…` | SPA fallback only for `/dashboard/*`, `/onboarding/*`, `/oauth/mcp/consent` |
| `/api/*` (most) | Per-handler session / token | See handler |
| Public marketing (`/`, `/work`, …) | **No** dashboard session | Served from `ASSET_ROUTES` + `env.ASSETS` |
| `/auth/login`, `/auth/signup`, `/auth/reset` | Public HTML shells | Worker `ASSET_ROUTES`; React also mounts auth in `App.tsx` |

**Not an auth bypass:** `/sitemap` returns **404** (globe page). The 404 template links to `/dashboard/agent` (“Back to Agent Sam”) — logged-in users land in dashboard; anonymous users get login redirect. Fix: add real `/sitemap.xml` + change 404 CTA to `/` for public paths.

